      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">This publication provides recommendations for using two vulnerability
                naming schemes: Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) and Common Configuration
                Enumeration (CCE). SP 800-51 Revision 1 gives an introduction to both naming schemes
                and makes recommendations for end-user organizations on using their names. The
                publication also presents recommendations for software and service vendors on how
                they should use vulnerability names and naming schemes in their product and service
                offerings.</abstract>
